Worst/Best Time to Visit Rwenzori Mountains: A Month By Month Guide. While the Rwenzori Mountains are accessible year-round, hikers should aim for the dry months of June–August and December–February to make the most of their mountain climbing experience.

A large number of hikers have recently expressed interest in learning when is the best time to ascend the Rwenzori Mountains, the third-highest peak in Africa. Located in western Uganda, close to the Uganda-Congo border, are the Rwenzori Mountains, sometimes called the Mountains of the Moon. Moorland, bamboo, and verdant, moist montane forest dominate the lower slopes, while the tropical snow summits comprise Africa’s third highest mountain. An lovely, fanciful scene is painted as massive lobelias and “everlasting flowers” scatter across the hillside, accompanied by massive tree heathers and rainbow mosses.

To walk with gorillas, you would need to visit one of the few places in the world where gorillas can be found in the wild, such as the Bwindi Impenetrable National Park, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park in Uganda, Volcanoes National Park in Rwanda & Virunga National Park, Kahuzi-Biéga National Park in Congo. These areas are often protected national parks or reserves, and permits are required to enter and observe the gorillas.

Once you have obtained a permit, you will be accompanied by a trained guide who will take you on a hike through the forest to find the gorillas. The hike can be challenging, as gorillas live in mountainous areas and the terrain can be steep and slippery. However, the reward of seeing these majestic animals in their natural habitat is well worth the effort
